A man and his dog walk through the woods. The dog leaps in excitement at the sight of a new home, while the man looks down at his feet, searching desperately to find a place to stick his finger on. When he finds it, he takes it in turns to lead the way, first him, then his dog, then himself. When he gets tired, he rests his head on his chest and weeps for a few more hours.

&#x200B;

This is a short story I wrote a few months ago. I had no idea it would get this far. I'm very happy with it. It has received a lot of love and support from my readers, who have helped me along the way. If you want to read it, please feel free. It's very short and sweet. I hope you enjoy it.

